Special Track Information
-------------------------

Call for Papers for the I-KNOW =C2=B407 special track on Knowledge Visualis=
ation=20
and Knowledge Discovery 2007

I-KNOW '07 special track on Knowledge Visualization and Knowledge Discovery=
=20
addresses the emerging fields of knowledge and information visualization,=
=20
knowledge discovery and information retrieval, involving discovery,=20
interaction with and visual presentation of abstract knowledge, information=
=20
spaces and structures to facilitate their rapid assimilation and=20
understanding. Original papers are solicited in all aforementioned areas.=
=20
Submissions will be reviewed by a board of international experts.=20


Topics
------

 * Visualisation of text and multimedia corpora=20
 * Visualisation of search results=20
 * Visualisation of web information systems=20
 * Visualisation of abstract information structures and spaces=20
 * Visualisation of knowledge and concept structures=20
 * Visualisation of knowledge relationships=20
 * Visualisation of temporal and spatial data=20
 * Mapping and editing of knowledge structures=20
 * Concept mapping=20
 * Human computer interfaces for knowledge and information visualisation=20
 * Visual representations and interaction techniques=20
 * Empirical studies of knowledge and information visualisation techniques=
=20
 * Perceptual factors for knowledge and information visualisation=20
 * Adaptive visualisation metaphors=20
 * Visual data mining=20
 * Visual analytics=20
 * Data structures, frameworks, and models underlying visualisation=20
 * Knowledge discovery and web mining techniques=20
 * Knowledge discovery from unstructured and multimedia data=20
 * Knowledge discovery supported by semantic technologies=20
 * Knowledge relationship discovery=20
 * Multi-relational mining and statistical relational learning=20
 * Clustering and classification techniques=20
 * Multimedia and cross-modal retrieval=20
 * Information and knowledge extraction=20
 * Information summarization=20
 * Intelligent network agents=20
 * Natural language processing=20
 * Topic detection and tracking=20
 * Data structures, frameworks, and models underlying knowledge discovery &=
=20
data mining=20
 * Service-oriented, semantic-enhanced software architectures for knowledge=
=20
discovery=20

Submissions might also address applications of knowledge discovery and=20
visualisation in areas such as mind mapping, decision support, e-learning,=
=20
CSCW, healthcare, virtual environments, search engines, mobile and pervasiv=
e=20
computing, or bioinformatics.=20


Target Group=20
------------

The topics mentioned above are addressed at researchers and developers as w=
ell=20
as at practitioners and providers in the fields of knowledge discovery and=
=20
knowledge and information visualization. The special track will be held in=
=20
English.=20


